rant.text: when people think you know everything...

comments.body: But at some point we all do it.

My desk is next to the main printer at my work. Everyone thinks that my desk is there specifically to fix their problems. Eventually, I wrote a sign in crayon (because printing would imply I have used it) "I can't fix your printer"
I fixed my grandmother's printer last week remotely. I had her unplug it and plug it back in after 30 secs lol.

I wish I could upvote this a thousand times.

Also, every Tom Dick and Harry wants to know "oh can you help me write an app", because of course I don't actually have a day job....

My teachers always ask us for the most ridiculous things just because we are in an IT course.

No teacher, I can't login to your son's Facebook account just because you want to know what he's up to with his friends.
